article.headline: Iowa 68, Louisiana-Monroe 40
article.story: IOWA CITY, Iowa -- Freshman Zach McCabe scored 12 points and Iowa beat Louisiana-Monroe 68-40 Tuesday night to give coach Fran McCaffery his first win with the Hawkeyes. Fellow freshman Melsahn Basabe had seven points, 11 rebounds and three blocks for Iowa (1-1), which bounced back from a season-opening loss to South Dakota State by dominating the Warhawks. The Hawkeyes led by 11 at halftime and quickly stretched their edge to 45-24 on Devyn Marble's layup with 12 minutes left. Iowa outscored ULM 39-22 in the second half to turn a relatively close game into a rout. Iowa played its second straight game without star junior guard Matt Gatens, who tore a tendon in his non-shooting hand last month but could return this weekend for the Paradise Jam in the U.S. Virgin Islands. Tommie Sykes had 14 points for ULM (0-2), which fell to 1-9 against Big Ten opponents.
